  "prompt": "How long did it take you to get a job after graduating?",
  "response": "The time it takes to get a job after graduating can vary greatly depending on factors such as the field of study, the job market, location, availability of opportunities, personal networking, and individual perseverance. Some graduates find jobs within a few months, while others may take up to a year or more. It's often beneficial to start networking early, gain relevant experience through internships, and actively seek out job opportunities during and after completing one's degree.",
